Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, here is something
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.90,0:00:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that should blow your
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.72,0:00:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.35,0:00:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Most AI video models
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.43,0:00:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,today are basically fancy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.90,0:00:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,pattern matchers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.04,0:00:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They can generate visually
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.13,0:00:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,stunning footage, but ask
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.67,0:00:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,them to reason about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.51,0:00:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,what
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.75,0:00:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually happening in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.06,0:00:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a video understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.50,0:00:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Spatial relationships navigate through
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.51,0:00:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a graph of objects,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.72,0:00:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize geometric patterns over
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.35,0:00:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,time, and they completely
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.62,0:00:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That is because we
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.42,0:00:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.76,0:00:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,had the right training
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.48,0:00:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,data to teach them
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.48,0:00:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,how to think visually.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.64,0:00:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now, I am
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.48,0:00:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.05,0:00:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,VBVR, very big video
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.62,0:00:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,reasoning, a data set
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.82,0:00:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that contains over 1
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.10,0:00:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,million video clips,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.37,0:00:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,spanning 200 curated reasoning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.98,0:00:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,tasks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.60,0:00:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't just a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.25,0:00:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,slide improvement over existing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.84,0:00:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,benchmarks.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.92,0:00:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about three
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.89,0:00:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,orders of magnitude more
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.28,0:00:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,data than what researchers
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.42,0:00:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,have been working with.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.70,0:00:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a massive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.46,0:00:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,leap toward teaching AI
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.88,0:00:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to actually understand video.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.74,0:00:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just generated,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.78,0:00:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and in this video,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.74,0:00:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I am going to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.32,0:00:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,break down exactly why
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.53,0:00:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,this matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.35,0:00:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is in the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.96,0:00:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,data set and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.70,0:00:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what the baseline model
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.71,0:00:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,results tell us about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.88,0:00:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the future of video
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.75,0:00:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.38,0:00:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.74,0:00:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about just
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.65,0:00:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,how massive this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.78,0:00:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.42,0:00:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,VBVR contains 1 million
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.89,0:01:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,video clips across 200
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.43,0:01:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,different reasoning tasks, and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.97,0:01:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,each of those tasks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.79,0:01:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is designed to test
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a specific aspect of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.40,0:01:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,visual intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.64,0:01:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now here is what
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.28,0:01:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,makes this truly unprecedented,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.18,0:01:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the data set includes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.15,0:01:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,100
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.84,0:01:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,task generators, each producing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.57,0:01:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,10 ,000 samples.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.51,0:01:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a million
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.12,0:01:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,carefully constructed examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.01,0:01:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one with a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.65,0:01:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,video, start, and end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.04,0:01:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,frames, a textual reasoning
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.56,0:01:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,prompt, and structured metadata,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.09,0:01:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,including the generator name,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.98,0:01:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,task name, and sample
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.18,0:01:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,ID.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.65,0:01:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is not
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.07,0:01:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,just about quantity,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.40,0:01:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the variety of tasks
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is what makes VBVR
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.59,0:01:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,special.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.29,0:01:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about spatial
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.34,0:01:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.26,0:01:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,where models need to
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.07,0:01:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,understand how objects relate
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.62,0:01:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to each other in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.43,0:01:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,3D space,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.50,0:01:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,graph navigation, where an
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.85,0:01:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,AI has to follow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.76,0:01:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and predict paths through
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.18,0:01:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,connected visual elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.93,0:01:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,pattern recognition across time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.85,0:01:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,geometric understanding that requires
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking shapes and their
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.95,0:01:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,transformations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.26,0:01:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is fundamentally different
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.48,0:01:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from existing video data
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.81,0:01:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sets that focus on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.00,0:01:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,visual
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,quality or captioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.81,0:01:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,VBVR is specifically designed
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.59,0:01:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to move beyond aesthetics
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.23,0:01:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and focus on
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.15,0:02:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,actual reasoning capabilities, and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.14,0:02:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that is exactly what
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.18,0:02:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the research community has
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.51,0:02:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,been missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.18,0:02:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so we have
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.90,0:02:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this massive data set,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.40,0:02:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,but how do we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.04,0:02:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,actually measure if a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.15,0:02:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,model is reasoning
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.02,0:02:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,correctly?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.75,0:02:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That is where VBVR
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.84,0:02:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,bench comes in, and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.00,0:02:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it is genuinely clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.28,0:02:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The benchmark provides
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.09,0:02:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a verifiable evaluation framework
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.31,0:02:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with rule -based human
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.91,0:02:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,aligned scorers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.13,0:02:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This means no subjective
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.43,0:02:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,human ratings.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.69,0:02:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No ambiguous quality assessments,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.74,0:02:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,hard metrics that tell
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.68,0:02:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you exactly how well
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.63,0:02:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a model
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.96,0:02:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,performs on each reasoning
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.18,0:02:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,task.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.80,0:02:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is crucial for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,reproducibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Other video reasoning benchmarks
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.25,0:02:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,often rely on human
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.81,0:02:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,evaluators, which introduces inconsistency,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.71,0:02:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes it hard
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.28,0:02:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to compare results
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.09,0:02:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,across studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.13,0:02:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,VBVR bench eliminates that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.06,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,problem with structured automated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,scoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.59,0:02:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The structured
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.03,0:02:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,metadata I mentioned earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.62,0:02:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,plays a big role
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.52,0:02:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.28,0:02:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Every sample includes the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.43,0:02:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,generator name,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.47,0:02:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,task name, sample ID
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.68,0:02:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,prompt, and paths to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.08,0:02:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,both video and image
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.28,0:02:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,data.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.00,0:02:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This means researchers can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.12,0:02:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,precisely identify which tasks
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.02,0:02:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a model struggles with
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.63,0:02:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and drill down into
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.68,0:02:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly why it is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.18,0:02:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,level of detail that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.53,0:03:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,enables systematic analysis of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.90,0:03:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,spatial temporal reasoning at
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.50,0:03:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.03,0:03:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now for the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.37,0:03:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,exciting part, what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.47,0:03:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when you actually train
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.50,0:03:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a model on this
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.36,0:03:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,data, meet VBVR 1R,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.34,0:03:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a baseline model
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.19,0:03:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,trained from 1R Genive
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.74,0:03:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,SOB without any architectural
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.37,0:03:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,modifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.36,0:03:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That is an important
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.03,0:03:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.84,0:03:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.86,0:03:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,researchers didn't invent a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.21,0:03:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,new model architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.50,0:03:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They just took an
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.19,0:03:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,existing video generation model
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.78,0:03:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and threw a million
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,reasoning examples at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and here is where
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.71,0:03:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it gets interesting early
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.06,0:03:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,signs of emergent generalization
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.80,0:03:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to unseen reasoning tasks
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.34,0:03:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,were observed in the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.65,0:03:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,scaling studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.65,0:03:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This means the model
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.74,0:03:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't just memorizing the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.28,0:03:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,training examples.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It was actually learning
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.53,0:03:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,reason in ways that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.58,0:03:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,transferred to tasks it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.97,0:03:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,had never seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.21,0:03:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a huge
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It suggests
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.65,0:03:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that as you scale
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.41,0:03:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,up video reasoning data,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.86,0:03:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,something fundamental shifts in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.18,0:03:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,what the model can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.87,0:03:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The research focus specifically
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,on investigating data scaling
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.71,0:03:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior, and the results
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.96,0:03:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,indicate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.41,0:03:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that more data doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.50,0:03:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,just mean better performance
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.78,0:03:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,on scene tasks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.12,0:03:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It means genuinely improved
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.68,0:03:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,reasoning capabilities that generalize
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.75,0:03:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.30,0:04:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is exactly what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.21,0:04:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the field needs to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.08,0:04:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,move toward
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.71,0:04:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,generalizable video intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.50,0:04:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,big picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.30,0:04:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,VBVR represents a fundamental
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.87,0:04:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,shift
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.40,0:04:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in how we approach
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.41,0:04:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,video intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.69,0:04:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of chasing better
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,visuals, we're now focusing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.93,0:04:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,on what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.62,0:04:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,actually matters reasoning in
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.41,0:04:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,spatiotemporally consistent visual environments.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.56,0:04:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,With over 1
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.33,0:04:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,million video clips, hardening
